@NODE "Inf" "TM-Brushes Background Information"

 ADPro: was a pretty long time on my ToDo-list, and well, I kind of finished
        it now. I painted it after a picture of Benjamin Franklin, 'cause I
        think he looks similar...maybe it IS Ben Franklin, but who knows...

 DPaintV: Another version of XENs Paint.brush. I'm not quite sure if it looks
          better...here it is anyway.

 Misc: I needed a dock-brush which opens a sub-dock in the ToolManager.

 SuperView: At last, I wasn't SO satisfied with the SuperView-icon in RI6,
            and some people requested a TM-brush for it, so this is the result.


 @{" Click here " SYSTEM "MultiView RIguide/TM.brush"} for the TMBrush overview.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Imd" "ImageDrawers Background Information"

 The right place for your LOCALE files. I'm sorry for swedish, spain (no yellow)
 and italian people (no green).

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Ico" "Icons Background Information"

 DirOpus: Standard size icon requested by Timo Kaikuman, it's a cut version
          of XENs original FileManager.brush.

 JukeBox: For the great CD audio player program by F.J.Reichert.

 HamLab: Requested by Timo Kaikuman.

 Thor: This is for you, Troels. It is taken from a Trevor Morris MWB Pattern-
       Pack and I think he ripped it from the game HeimdallII.

 RI.guide: The alternate pic shows how I look for real. :-[

@ENDNODE

